# List of Tiangong Space Station expeditions

This is a chronological list of permanent expeditions to the Tiangong space station (TSS), a space station operated by China in low Earth orbit since 2021. An expedition to the TSS refers to the crew that is occupying the space station and using it for research and testing. Expeditions can last up to six months and typically include three crewmembers. Starting with Expedition 3 (Shenzhou 14), expeditions have overlapped so that the station remains continuously inhabited.
Expeditions are numbered starting from one and sequentially increased with each expedition. TSS commanders are listed in bold. "Duration" is the period of time between the crew's arrival and departure from the TSS
